Step 1: Start.
Step 2: Accept a range of numbers between m and n.
Step 3: Verify if m <1 or m>10 or n<1 or n>10 
Step 4: If step 3 is true stop.
Step 5: Accept elements of matrix mat[][].
Step 6: Display original matrix.
Step 7: Short every row of the matrix using bubble sort technique.
Step 8: Print the sorted matrix.
Step 9: Stop.
